issues.description: The `calculateTotalPrice` method is declared in the problem statement to return a double, but in the solution it is implemented to return an int. This mismatch prevents students from returning a double precision result as specified and will cause signature conflicts with the exercise tests.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the return type of `calculateTotalPrice` from int to double in the SealSaloon class (update the method signature and accumulate the sum in a double variable) to match the specification.
